Relationships are relationships, and communication is the key to them. Oddly enough, communication is the main thing going on in the net, and in EQ in particular. EQ is a community, just like any other. Think of FV as your local gaming club. You go there (some more, some less), you hang out with people, yoy play with them, and you go home. With some of them, you'll never speak again, or not in a few years. With some, you might discover a lifetime friendship. Same thing. <br>
Having the connection be virtual changes a few characteristics, but not too many. You find it harder to share food/drink, but on the other hand, you're less influenced by external appearances (looks, clothes, jewlery, whatever), and get a deeper more meaningful impression of the other person first. <br>
Yeah, you can be deceived over a virtual communication channel. But then, you can be deceived in a face to face meeting too. The difference is not as great as you think.<br>
<br>
Brora, that sounds like a fascinating subject to be studying. Lucky you <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=95331" target="_new">
