hmmm.<br>
<br>
My point is if you do not establish irl contact with an in game friend, if the fragile thread of communication which is the game or either of your access to the game is changed you lose communication with said person.<br>
<br>
Your only means of communication which is through your toons name <br>
<br>
If they were truly a friend, I would think you would want to secure a more permanent relationship with them, unless you are interested in only having a temporary friend.<br>
<br>
Another aspect of the online friend : you only know them by the text they send to you.  You lose the communication you get from body language and voice inflection/tone.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
On a different note, once you trust a toon in game who you think is your &quot;friend&quot; by loaning them alot of hard earned gear for a month, someone whom you have spent countless hours and countless levels with, and then when you want the gear back, they take off with your gear to never return, you will better understand and redefine who you call a friend.<br>
