<br>
It *is* a fascinating subject to study, and it's getting really big in the communication field right now, but I get a lot of &quot;oooookay&quot;s from more traditional academics and non-Comm folk alike.  You should have seen the looks on my Basic Communication students' faces when I told them I research how people communicate while playing online video games...  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
But hey, where else can I get college credit for writing a research paper on in-group closeness among role playing gamers in both face-to-face and computer-mediated contexts, eh?  Or an analysis of the socio-cultural implications of blogging among the academic elite?<br>
<br>
Life is good.<br>
